Package solvers.wfc

Class WaveFunctionCollapse

java.lang.Object
solvers.Solver
solvers.wfc.WaveFunctionCollapse
public class WaveFunctionCollapse extends Solver
Implements the Wave Function Collapse algorithm to solve Sudoku puzzles.

This solver is based on Maxim Gumin's work on the Wave Function Collapse (WFC) algorithm. It applies WFC, a constraint satisfaction algorithm, to find a solution to a given Sudoku grid. The solver iteratively collapses cells with the minimum entropy until a solution is found or a contradiction is encountered, requiring a rollback.

  • Method Details

    • fillEntropy

      private void fillEntropy()
      Initializes the entropy matrix for the Sudoku grid.

      For each cell, if it's empty, the entropy is set to the number of possible values it can hold. If the cell is already filled, the entropy is set to -1.

    • rollBack

      protected void rollBack()
      Rolls back the last move by resetting the symbol in the last inserted cell.

      This method retrieves the last inserted position from lastInserts, resets the symbol in the grid at that position, and updates the history. It also propagates the entropy change caused by removing the symbol.
